Install Argo CD using Helm, but:

CRDs are already installed

You must not install CRDs again

You must generate a Helm template and save it to /argo-helm.yaml

Use version 7.7.3

Install in argocd namespace

Release name: argocd

ğŸ”¥ Step 1 â€” Add the Argo Helm repo
helm repo add argo https://argo.github.io/argo-helm
helm repo update

ğŸ”¥ Step 2 â€” Generate the template with CRDs disabled
helm template argocd argo/argo-cd \
  --version 7.7.3 \
  --namespace argocd \
  --set crds.install=false \
  > /argo-helm.yaml


This creates the full YAML with CRDs disabled, saved to /argo-helm.yaml.

ğŸ”¥ Step 3 â€” Install using that exact template (same config)
helm install argocd argo/argo-cd \
  --version 7.7.3 \
  --namespace argocd \
  --create-namespace \
  --set crds.install=false

âœ… Result

Argo CD installed

Same version as the template

Same config

CRDs not installed

Namespace argocd

Release name argocd

If you want the â€œpure YAML onlyâ€ approach (apply the generated file), that works too, but the exam wants Helm commands, not kubectl apply.
